com.intellij.diagram

Interface DiagramVisibilityManager

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractUmlVisibilityManager, EmptyDiagramVisibilityManager

    public interface DiagramVisibilityManager
    Visibility Manager handles node content representation. For instance, all components of a node are class members. And each of them has a visibility level: public, protected, package local or private. Visibility Manager helps to show only, say public, members.
    Author:
    Konstantin Bulenkov
